The Lagos State University (LASU) has urged Akinbiyi Abiola Ahmed aka Bella Shmurda to return for the completion of his degree programme at the institution. The 25-year-old artiste had stated that he failed some courses while at the institution, forcing him to quit school. He became popular after the release of his debut single ‘Vision 2020’ after he featured Olamide in the remix version. Bella has since released hit songs like Cash App featuring Zlatan and many others.   Trader gets wish for divorce because husband loves his dog…     PHOTOS: Suspended DCP Abba Kyari makes first public…     BREAKING: Suspended DCP Abba Kyari makes first public…   - Advertisement - He wrote: I now worth over half a billion streams (550millions streams to be precise). I for still Dey lasu Dey wine and dine with carryovers and stranded with nothing in my pocket… forever glad I did my thing.  Reacting, LASU on its official Twitter handle said: Happy birthday @fineboybella. Glad you have come this far pursuing your dream. “Also glad @LASUOfficial played a part in your beautiful story because Univ. dont make people rich, only incubate them to find and achieve purpose. BTW, please come back to class and earn your degree.”